What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Plastic Additives Market?



Market Analysis and Size

Plastic additives are the type of ingredients which act as a catalyst or fillers that are added in polymers to improve their sensitivity, durability, and strength. Plasticizers, fillers, antioxidants and impact modifiers among others are the major types of plastic additives.

Increase in the disposable income and rapid urbanization is the vital factor escalating the market growth, also rise in the rapid growth in food packaging industries, increase in the low price and high durability of plastic and increase in the technology advancement are the major factors among others driving the plastic additives market. Moreover, rise in the technological advancements and modernization in the production techniques and rise in the demand from emerging economies will further create new opportunities for the plastic additives market in the forecast period of 2023 to 2030.

However, rise in the stringent governmental regulations regarding environmental concern and fluctuating raw materials pricing are the major factors among others acting as restraints, and will further challenge the growth of plastic additives market in the forecast period mentioned above.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global plastic additives market which was USD 43.90 billion in 2022, is expected to reach USD 68.08 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 5.8% during the forecast period of 2023 to 2030. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.



